You can use one of the many libraries designed to facilitate precondition checks. Many code in [Google Guava][1] uses [`com.google.common.base.Preconditions`](https://guava.dev/releases/19.0/api/docs/com/google/common/base/Preconditions.html)

&gt; Simple static methods to be called at the start of your own methods to verify correct arguments and state. This allows constructs such as
&gt; 
&gt;      if (count &lt;= 0) {
&gt;        throw new IllegalArgumentException(&quot;must be positive: &quot; + count);
&gt;      }
&gt; 
