&gt;      checkArgument(count &gt; 0, &quot;must be positive: %s&quot;, count);

It has [`checkNotNull`](http://guava-libraries.googlecode.com/svn-history/r13/trunk/javadoc/com/google/common/base/Preconditions.html#checkNotNull%28T%29) that is [used extensively within Guava](https://github.com/google/guava/search?q=checkNotNull). You can then write:

     import static com.google.common.base.Preconditions.checkNotNull;
