answers.body_markdown:
&gt; Do I need to write a new Serializer for the Type List&lt;Student&gt; or can
&gt; I reuse StudentSerializer

You can reuse the `StudentSerializer` serializer already defined: in your case you can annotate your `students`field in the `Course` class with the `JsonSerialize` annotation with [`contentUsing`](https://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-databind/javadoc/2.14/com/fasterxml/jackson/databind/annotation/JsonSerialize.html#contentUsing--) directive where `contentusing` indicates the serializer class to use for serializing contents (elements of a Collection/array, values of Maps) of one annotated property:

~~~
class Course(
    var id: Long? = null,
    var name: String? = null,
    @JsonSerialize(contentUsing= StudentSerializer::class)
    var students: MutableList&lt;Student&gt; = mutableListOf()
)
~~~

